    • My Dog's Nose
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Brighter than expected, great lights
      Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2021
      Color: Rgb (Red, Green, Blue)Size: 6IN-4P-RD
      Bought 8 of these to install on my back deck ceiling. Technically I guess I bought 12 since I bought an extra box just to have on hand in case one dies a few years from now, but I only installed 8. I probably should have looked closer at the light output, because wow is... See more
      Bought 8 of these to install on my back deck ceiling. Technically I guess I bought 12 since I bought an extra box just to have on hand in case one dies a few years from now, but I only installed 8. I probably should have looked closer at the light output, because wow is it bright. I had to change the preset to only turn on at 30 percent to make my eyes not burn at 4:00 a.m. when the dogs want to go out. Installation is pretty basic. Install your wire clamp or conduit into the box, connect your hot, neutral, and ground to the pre-installed wire connectors (which I like better than traditional caps tbh. You can buy them at any home improvement store), plug the cable from the light to the box, and you're good to go. The installed wire nut has room for one more set of wires so you can connect more lights in series, just like your wiring any other light fixture. The app can get a little finicky during discovery, especially because when it detects all the lights they all have the same name, so you have to turn them off in the app one by one to figure out which is which. Overall I really like them, and love the way they look. No problems controlling them either through the app or Alexa. I have them on a standard house switch, so when I turn them on they default to White, then throughout the night I can set the colors and brightness as I desire. It's pretty cool to set them to Black (more just blue tbh) at 10%, and sit outside with the propane fire table turned on while enjoying a cool drink on a summer night. Turn off the switch and they're back to white next time they're turned on. That is a very useful feature. I definitely recommend these as an alternative to traditional can lights.

      Edited for typos and an update:
      After about a month or so of these, we still love them. I've noticed sometimes they get touchy, and of the 8 I have in a group, sometimes 1 or 2 do not dim/change via Alexa as expected. When this happens (rare, but sometimes), I just turn off the switch to reset them, turn it back on, wait 30 seconds, then dim/change them again. I assume it's just a delay with the light connecting to wifi. Great product and I look forward to using them for many years.

      If you are using just a few lights, it is probably fine. I installed roughly 50 of the lights in our house as part of a remodel. I have had them installed for 18 months at this point. These are wifi-connected lights, so anytime they can't connect, they begin to... See more
      If you are using just a few lights, it is probably fine. I installed roughly 50 of the lights in our house as part of a remodel. I have had them installed for 18 months at this point. These are wifi-connected lights, so anytime they can't connect, they begin to flash/strobe at the brightest setting. This is awful when you have people over or are trying to turn the lights on in a bedroom.

      After reading into this, I upgraded to a new mesh wireless network ($550) and still had the issue. Next, I moved all the lights to Home Assistant and tried to operate the lights locally to solve the connectivity issue. This did not work either and took about 15 hours of programming. I am in the process of ripping them all out and replacing them with Philips Hue. Zero issues with the Philips hue lights. Bottom line, don't buy this if you are using more than four lights.
